tripleoclient/utils.py.message:
I think best would be to have this piece of code to either use "safe ifs" or try/except

one option to avoid try/except could be:

  if "resource_registry" in content and content["resource_registry"]:
    for service in constants.DEPRECATED_SERVICES.keys():
      if service in content["resource_registry"] and content["resource_registry"][service] != "OS::Heat::None":
        LOG.warn

alternatively to rely on try/except instead

  for service in constants.DEPRECATED_SERVICES.keys():
    try:
      if content["resource_registry"][service] != "OS::Heat::None":
        LOG.warn
    except (KeyError, TypeError) as e:
      pass

I think I prefer the latter

